    <Content>
      The system shall classify each requirement as either a Functional Requirement (FR) or a Non-Functional Requirement (NFR) in the &lt;Type&gt; tag and shall not use combined type labels such as "NFR / FR", thereby ensuring that the example requirement is treated purely as documentation and not implemented as a functional feature.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- Exploration control and behavior (HL-EXPL-1.2) -->

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-1.2.1">
