[2026-05-13--21:43:05]Agent: <Requirements version="2" hierarchy="LLR">
  <!-- Exploration control and behavior (HL-EXPL-1.2) -->

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-1.2.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Autonomous Exploration Mode</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall provide an "Exploration" operating mode in which the robot shall autonomously navigate the maze without manual control input after a start command is issued.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-1.2.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Start Condition</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall start the autonomous exploration mode only after receiving a start signal via a designated user interface or control input and confirming that all required sensors and actuators are in an operational state.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-1.2.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Termination Conditions</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.3</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall terminate exploration mode when at least one of the following conditions is met: (a) all reachable cells in the maze are mapped as FREE or BLOCKED; (b) a predefined exploration time limit, not exceeding 5 minutes, is reached; or (c) a stop command is received from the user interface.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-1.2.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Coverage Strategy</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      During exploration mode, the system shall apply a deterministic coverage strategy, such as flood-fill or frontier-based exploration, that repeatedly selects the next navigation target among currently reachable UNKNOWN cells until no such UNKNOWN cell remains reachable.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-1.2.5">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Localization Update</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-6.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      During exploration, the system shall continuously estimate the robot's current pose (position and orientation) within the maze coordinate system using wheel odometry and, if available, additional sensors, and shall update this pose estimate at a fixed rate of at least 10 Hz.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- Wall detection and avoidance (HL-EXPL-1.3, HL-RELIAB-5.1) -->

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-1.3.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Wall Presence Detection</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-6.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall detect the presence of a wall in front, left, and right of the robot by processing the configured distance or proximity sensors and shall provide a Boolean wall flag for each observed direction in the internal state at a minimum rate of 20 Hz.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-1.3.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Wall Distance Thresholds</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-RELIAB-5.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-6.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall treat any obstacle detected within a configurable safety distance threshold, expressed in centimeters, as a wall and shall store this threshold as a parameter that can be set at configuration time without code changes.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-1.3.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Collision-Free Motion Command Generation</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-RELIAB-5.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-6.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The motion control subsystem shall generate translational and rotational velocity commands such that no commanded trajectory allows the robot's chassis to intersect a region classified as a wall in the internal map or currently detected as a wall by sensors.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-1.3.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Emergency Stop on Imminent Collision</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-RELIAB-5.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-6.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-6.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall issue an immediate stop command to the drive actuators whenever sensor data indicates that the measured distance to a wall in the direction of motion is less than a predefined emergency distance threshold.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-1.3.5">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Wall Avoidance Maneuver</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-RELIAB-5.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      When a wall is detected within the safety distance along the current heading, the system shall plan and execute an avoidance maneuver that either turns the robot in place or steers it toward a FREE neighboring cell while maintaining a non-collision trajectory.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- Map representation and maintenance (HL-MAP-2.1, HL-MAP-2.2, HL-MAP-2.3) -->

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-2.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Discrete Maze Grid Representation</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall represent the maze as a discrete grid of cells with a configurable cell size and a finite maximum grid dimension that shall be configurable but not less than 16 by 16 cells and not greater than 64 by 64 cells, where the configured maximum dimension shall be chosen to cover the maximum maze width and height specified in the system configuration.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-2.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Cell State Model</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      Each cell in the maze grid shall have a state field that shall be one of {UNKNOWN, FREE, BLOCKED, UNCERTAIN}, and the initial state of all cells shall be UNKNOWN before exploration starts.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-2.1.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Map Update from Sensor Observations</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-6.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-RELIAB-5.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      For each valid distance sensor reading, the system shall project the corresponding sensor beam into the maze grid using a discrete ray-casting algorithm and shall update cell states as follows: (a) cells along the beam from the sensor origin up to but not including the cell at the detected obstacle distance shall be marked FREE unless they are currently BLOCKED; and (b) the cell corresponding to the detected obstacle distance shall be marked BLOCKED unless the reading has been classified as uncertain by the fault-tolerance mechanism, in which case the cell shall be marked UNCERTAIN.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-2.1.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Consistency of Cell Classification</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-RELIAB-5.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      Once a cell is classified as BLOCKED, the system shall not reclassify it as FREE, and once a cell is classified as FREE, the system shall not reclassify it as BLOCKED; if conflicting sensor readings are received that would require such a reclassification, the system shall instead set the cell state to UNCERTAIN and shall retain both FREE and BLOCKED evidence for use by the fault-tolerance mechanism.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-2.1.5">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Map Origin and Start Cell</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-RUN-4.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall define the robot's initial position at the start of exploration as the origin of the maze coordinate system and shall store the corresponding grid cell index as the start cell.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-2.1.6">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Cell Uncertainty Management</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-RELIAB-5.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall maintain for each cell a confidence value in the range 0 to 1 for being BLOCKED and a confidence value for being FREE, shall mark a cell as UNCERTAIN when both confidences are within a configurable intermediate range, and shall transition a cell from UNCERTAIN to BLOCKED or FREE when the corresponding confidence exceeds a configurable decision threshold.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-2.3.1">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Mapping Time Constraint Management</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall maintain an exploration timer starting at the beginning of exploration mode and shall ensure that the exploration termination logic is capable of stopping exploration such that the mapping process completes within 5 minutes of timer start for mazes up to 16 by 16 cells with at most 50 percent of cells being dead ends, executed on the reference hardware platform specified in the system configuration, with no sensor or actuator faults present.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-2.3.2">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Time-Bounded Planning and Control Cycles</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-PLAN-3.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall limit the execution time of each exploration planning and control loop iteration so that the combined cycle time, including sensor processing, map update, path planning, and command output, does not exceed 100 milliseconds.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- Path planning (HL-PLAN-3.1) -->

  <Requirement ID="LL-PLAN-3.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Grid-Based Path Planning</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-PLAN-3.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall compute paths as sequences of adjacent FREE cells in the maze grid, treating BLOCKED and UNCERTAIN cells as non-traversable in all modes, and treating UNKNOWN cells as non-traversable for planned optimal runs including the second run.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-PLAN-3.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Planning Use of Unknown Cells</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-PLAN-3.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      During exploration mode, the system shall allow path planning to use UNKNOWN cells as navigation targets by planning paths through FREE cells to frontier cells that are adjacent to at least one UNKNOWN cell, while still prohibiting stepping directly into cells currently classified as BLOCKED or UNCERTAIN.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-PLAN-3.1.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Path Optimality Criterion</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-PLAN-3.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall define path optimality in terms of minimum total path cost, where path cost is at least the sum of per-step costs proportional to the Manhattan distance between successive grid cells, and may include additional penalties for turns.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-PLAN-3.1.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Shortest Path Algorithm</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-PLAN-3.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall implement a deterministic graph search algorithm, such as Dijkstra or A*, to compute the minimal-cost path on the grid from a start cell to a target cell using the defined path cost metric.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-PLAN-3.1.5">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Replanning Capability</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-PLAN-3.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall support replanning of a path whenever the map is updated with new BLOCKED or UNCERTAIN cells that intersect or invalidate the current planned path.
